==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Processioner
<hw>Pro*ces"sion*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>One who takes part in a procession.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A manual of processions; a processional.</def>
<rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An officer appointed to procession lands.</def>
<mark>[Local, U. S. (North Carolina and Tennessee).]</mark>
<rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Processioning</ent>⟦br⟧
